venezuela will seek 2.4 billion dollarsin export financing during 1987, double the amount it receivedlast year, public finance director jorge marcano said.    Marcano told reporters at the finance ministry yesterdaythat the 2.4 billion is part of a total package of 3.2 billiondlrs in new credits, which venezuela will try to obtain.    "we've begun efforts to secure that financing," he said. Reuter&#3;